            <span class="utterance" who="#brinI" start="1047.463" end="x">Well, it was seven in the morning. [unintelligible] There were no more people in the <a class="term" href="#vothG_ghetto">Ghetto</a>. Everything was already emptied out, and a truck came in covered . . . and every . . . with people. The people, who were going to be shot, were lying stretched out on the bottom of the truck. The crew, the German <a class="term" href="#vothG_gestapo">Gestapo</a>, the totenkopf,<note n="3"><span class="note">Totenkopf is the German word for "skull." A design featuring a skull and cross-bones was part of the Nazi SS uniforms.</span><sup><a href="#note_3">3</a></sup></note> as they were called, were sitting on them.</span>
