            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Itzhak Brin</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#brinI" start="2145.079" end="x">The leader of the camp came on the night of the 16th of January, came into the camp. "Children," he said, "Jews, save yourselves, each one of you, if you can." I [unintelligible] there was a place for eight people, and we went there and they took us in. In addition, we took along people whom we knew—we were twenty in all—and because we knew that we would not be there long, because we knew that the Russians were already in <a class="placename" href="#vothL91">Chenstokhov</a>, we went into the bunker and they hid us there.</span>
        </li>
